
[1]festival

   FES'TIVAL, a. [L. festivus, from festus, or festum or fasti. See
   Feast.]

   Pertaining to a feast; joyous; mirthful; as a festival entertainment.

   FES'TIVAL, n. The time of feasting; an anniversary day of joy, civil or
                                 religious.

   The morning trumpets festival proclaimed.
